 data, which couples\n\npersistence behavior to concrete command classes and makes extension harder.\n\nAdd a command-level shouldPersist() contract and use it in SpendSwift\n\nto trigger storage saves after mutating commands.\n\nAdd Storage tests for save/load round-trip, malformed lines, and\n\ninvalid amount lines to verify the integration behavior.\n","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{"functional-code":{"insertions":40,"deletions":7},"test-code":{"insertions":65,"deletions":0}}},{"hash":"1442c4fc8395902aa0305e22a8d810f6a7854a15","isMergeCommit":false,"messageTitle":"Harden parser, storage, and model defensiveness","messageBody":"The integration flow needs stronger runtime safety at parser/model/storage\n\nboundaries for invalid inputs and edge cases.\n\nAdd guard clauses and explicit IllegalArgumentException checks for\n\nnull/invalid values, validate delete index and add amount constraints,\n\nand add Storage logging for load/save parse failures.\n\nEnable assertions for Gradle run with -ea and extend tests to cover\n\nnew defensive behaviors and failure paths.\n","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{"functional-code":{"insertions":83,"deletions":11},"other":{"insertions":2,"deletions":1},"test-code":{"insertions":93,"deletions":4}}},{"hash":"5af62305fe7f364ae77ecf917c48d8c48c9f9d84","isMergeCommit":true,"messageTitle":"Merge pull request #37 from AnnikaGarg/branch-assert","messageBody":"Add Java assert statements in AddCommand and HelpCommand","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{}},{"hash":"29ff725902caa6d9876860815d08d3e15f9dd353","isMergeCommit":true,"messageTitle":"Merge remote-tracking branch \u0027upstream/master\u0027 into refactor-command-flow","messageBody":"","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{}},{"hash":"82d39ee173977c4cca6e00259c0ae5161c9d4c60","isMergeCommit":true,"messageTitle":"Merge branch \u0027refactor-command-flow\u0027 into storage-flow-integration","messageBody":"","fileTypesAndContributionMap":{}},{"hash":"f65f023af3f5470c1fd583a21b24e099ea96d03d","isMergeC